@startuml seq-10-document-read-download
title GET /documents/:documentId/versions/:versionId/file

actor "User" as U <<human>>
participant "Browser" as B <<browser>>
participant "Express\n/documents" as API <<service>>
participant "authenticateToken +\nrequireDocLibraryAccess" as MW <<service>>
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "documentAccess\n(canReadDocument)" as ACC <<service>>
participant "Local filesystem" as FS <<service>>

B -> API: GET .../versions/:versionId/file\nBearer + optional ?inline=

API -> MW: authenticate + library access
alt Unauthorized / library blocked
  API --> B: 401 / 403
else OK
  API -> DB: documentVersion.findUnique\ninclude document
  alt Wrong ids / not found
    API --> B: 404
  else Found
    API -> ACC: canReadDocument(user, document)
    alt Forbidden
      API --> B: 403 Forbidden
    else Allowed
      API -> FS: createReadStream(absolutePathForKey)
      API -> API: Set Content-Type,\nContent-Disposition inline/attachment
      FS --> B: Stream bytes (pipe)
    end
  end
end

note right of API
  Source: **apps/api/src/routes/documents.ts** (~1017+),
  **documentAccess.ts** (**canReadDocument**).
  Router applies **authenticateToken** +\n**requireDocLibraryAccess** for routes\nregistered after **documentsRouter.use**.\nThis route is under that middleware.
end note

@enduml
